{"warnings":{"query":{"*":"Formatting of continuation data will be changing soon. To continue using the current formatting, use the 'rawcontinue' parameter. To begin using the new format, pass an empty string for 'continue' in the initial query."}},"query":{"pages":{"2620746":{"pageid":2620746,"ns":0,"title":"Kleinstocks","revisions":[{"contentformat":"text/x-wiki","contentmodel":"wikitext","*":"{{Superherobox| <!--Wikipedia:WikiProject Comics--> \nimage=<!-- Deleted image removed: [[Image:Kleinstocks 1.jpg|120px|{{deletable image-caption|1=Saturday, 15 March 2008}}]] -->\n|caption=The Kleinstock Brothers.  Art by Casey Jones.\n|comic_color=background:#ff8080 \n|character_name=Kleinstock Brothers\n|real_name=Sven, Harlan, and Eric Kleinstock\n|species=[[Mutant (Marvel Comics)|Human Mutant]]\n|publisher=[[Marvel Comics]] \n|debut=''[[Uncanny X-Men]]'' #298 (March 1993)\n|creators=[[Scott Lobdell]]<br>[[Brandon Peterson]]\n|alliance_color=background:#c0c0ff\n|alliances=[[Acolytes (comics)|Acolytes]]\n|aliases=\n|powers=Explosive plasma blasts,<br />Flight<br>When merged: Superhuman size, strength, speed, stamina, sturdiness\n|}}\n\nThe '''Kleinstocks''' were a set of [[multiple birth|triplets]] that are [[comic book]] [[fictional character]]s, and are [[Mutant (Marvel Comics)|mutant]] [[supervillain]]s, in the [[Marvel Comics]] [[Marvel Universe|universe]]. The three brothers' names are '''Harlan''', '''Sven''' and '''Eric''', and they were created by [[Scott Lobdell]] and [[Brandon Peterson]] and first appeared in ''[[Uncanny X-Men]]'' #298 (March 1993).\n\n==Fictional character biography==\nIn their first mission with the [[Acolytes (comics)|Acolytes]], they were sent along with [[Cargill (comics)|Cargill]] and [[Unuscione|Carmella Unuscione]] to kidnap a young mutant. While attempting the kidnapping, they murdered [[Sharon Friedlander]], a former staff member at [[Professor X|Charles Xavier]]'s [[X-Mansion|School for Gifted Youngsters]]. In the moment before she died, Sharon managed to send a [[psionic]] cry for help to Xavier. Based upon this, Xavier sent a squad of X-Men to investigate. During the battle between the Acolytes and the X-Men, Eric was shot and killed by [[Tom Corsi]], another former staff member from Xavier's school. After discovering the mutant they were sent to kidnap had [[Down syndrome]], the Acolytes abandoned their mission.{{Issue|date=April 2010}}\n\nDespite losing their brother, Harlan and Sven continued to serve with the Acolytes. During the destruction of [[Providence (comics)|Avalon]] by [[Holocaust (comics)|Holocaust]], the surviving two were among the Acolytes who evacuated to Earth with the X-Man [[Cyclops (comics)|Cyclops]]. They crash landed in the [[Australian Outback]], where they managed to get to the X-Men's former base of operations. Once help arrived, they turned themselves over to the authorities.{{Issue|date=April 2010}}\n\nThey were able to escape prison and rejoined the Acolytes under the leadership of [[Fabian Cortez]]. These Acolytes were involved in attacks on [[Wundagore|Wundagore mountain]]. Some time later, they were involved in an attack on the [[X-Mansion]] with a group of Acolytes. At the end of the battle, they asked for sanctuary with Xavier, which was denied. They eventually rejoined the Acolytes under [[Magneto (comics)|Magneto]]'s command, when he was given leadership over [[Genosha]].{{Issue|date=April 2010}}\n\n==In other media==\n===Television===\n* The Kleinstock Brothers appear in the ''[[Wolverine and the X-Men (TV series)|Wolverine and the X-Men]]'' episode \"Battle Lines\". They are part of [[Magneto (comics)|Magneto]]'s Acolytes and are shown breaking mutants out of MRD Facility Delta in the south.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.marvel.com/universe/Kleinstock_Brothers Kleinstock Brothers] at Marvel.com\n* [http://www.uncannyxmen.net/glossary/showentry.asp?fldAuto=619 Uncannyxmen.net character bio on Kleinstock Brothers]\n\n[[